column1: Instability troubled the early years of Kublai Khan's reign. Ogedei's grandson Kaidu refused to submit to Kublai and threatened the western frontier of Kublai's domain. The hostile but weakened Song dynasty remained an obstacle in the south. Kublai secured the northeast border in 1259 by installing the hostage prince Wonjong as the ruler of Korea, making it a Mongol tributary state. Kublai was also threatened by domestic unrest. Li Tan, the son-in-law of a powerful official, instigated a revolt against Mongol rule in 1262. After successfully suppressing the revolt, Kublai curbed the influence of the Han Chinese advisers in his court. He feared that his dependence on Chinese officials left him vulnerable to future revolts and defections to the Song.
column2: Nestabilnost je povzročala težave v zgodnjih letih Kublajkanovega vladanja. Ogedejev vnuk Kaidu se ni hotel podrediti Kublajkanu in je ogrožal zahodno mejo Kublajkanove domene. Sovražna, a oslabljena dinastija Song je ostajala težava na jugu. Kublajkan je leta 1259 zavaroval severovzhodno mejo z namestitvijo talca, princa Wonjonga, kot vladarja Koreje, zaradi česar je postala mongolska tributarna država. Kublajkanu so grozili tudi domači nemiri. Li Tan, zet vplivnega uradnika, je leta 1262 sprožil upor proti mongolski vladavini. Po uspešnem zatoru upora je Kublajkan zajezil vpliv kitajskih svetovalcev Han na svojem dvoru. Bal se je, da je zaradi odvisnosti od kitajskih uradnikov ranljiv za prihodnje upore in prebege v dinastijo Song.

column1: It is conjectured that a progressive decline in hormone levels with age is partially responsible for weakened immune responses in aging individuals. Conversely, some hormones are regulated by the immune system, notably thyroid hormone activity. The age-related decline in immune function is also related to decreasing vitamin D levels in the elderly. As people age, two things happen that negatively affect their vitamin D levels. First, they stay indoors more due to decreased activity levels. This means that they get less sun and therefore produce less cholecalciferol via UVB radiation. Second, as a person ages the skin becomes less adept at producing vitamin D.
column2: Domneva se, da je postopno zmanjšanje ravni hormonov s starostjo delno odgovorno za oslabljen imunski odziv pri starajočih posameznikih. Nasprotno nekatere hormone imunski sistem uravnava, zlasti delovanje ščitničnega hormona. S starostjo povezano zmanjšanje imunske funkcije je povezano tudi z zniževanjem ravni vitamina D pri starejših. Ko se ljudje starajo, se zgodita dve stvari, ki negativno vplivata na raven vitamina D. Prvič, zaradi zmanjšane ravni aktivnosti več časa preživijo v zaprtih prostorih. To pomeni, da so manj izpostavljeni soncu in zato proizvajajo manj holekalciferola preko UVB sevanja. Drugič, ko se oseba stara, koža postane manj sposobna proizvodnje vitamina D.

column1: The university operates 12 research institutes and 113 research centers on campus. Among these are the Oriental Institute—a museum and research center for Near Eastern studies owned and operated by the university—and a number of National Resource Centers, including the Center for Middle Eastern Studies. Chicago also operates or is affiliated with a number of research institutions apart from the university proper. The university partially manages Argonne National Laboratory, part of the United States Department of Energy's national laboratory system, and has a joint stake in Fermilab, a nearby particle physics laboratory, as well as a stake in the Apache Point Observatory in Sunspot, New Mexico. Faculty and students at the adjacent Toyota Technological Institute at Chicago collaborate with the university, In 2013, the university announced that it was affiliating the formerly independent Marine Biological Laboratory in Woods Hole, Mass. Although formally unrelated, the National Opinion Research Center is located on Chicago's campus.
column2: Univerza na kampusu vodi 12 raziskovalnih inštitutov in 113 raziskovalnih centrov. Med njimi so Orientalski inštitut – muzej in raziskovalni center za bližnjevzhodne študije v lasti in upravljanju univerze – in številne nacionalne centre, vključno s Centrom za bližnjevzhodne študije. Univerza Chicago prav tako vodi ali je povezana s številnimi raziskovalnimi ustanovami izven univerze. Univerza delno upravlja nacionalni laboratorij Argonne, ki je del nacionalnega laboratorijskega sistema ameriškega ministrstva za energijo, in ima skupni delež v Fermilabu, bližnjem laboratoriju za fiziko osnovnih delcev, kot tudi delež v observatoriju Apache Point v Sunspotu, Novi Mehiki. Fakulteta in študenti na sosednjem Tehnološkem inštitutu Toyota v Chicagu sodelujejo z univerzo. Leta 2013 je univerza razglasila, da se povezuje s prej neodvisnim morskim biološkim laboratorijem v Woods Holu, Massachusettsu. Čeprav je formalno nepovezan, se raziskovalni inštitut National Opinion Research Center nahaja na kampusu univerze Chicago.

column1: The weight of boilers and condensers generally makes the power-to-weight ratio of a steam plant lower than for internal combustion engines. For mobile applications steam has been largely superseded by internal combustion engines or electric motors. However, most electric power is generated using steam turbine plant, so that indirectly the world's industry is still dependent on steam power. Recent concerns about fuel sources and pollution have incited a renewed interest in steam both as a component of cogeneration processes and as a prime mover. This is becoming known as the Advanced Steam movement.[citation needed]
column2: Zaradi teže kotlov in kondenzatorjev je razmerje med močjo in težo naprave za uparjevanje na splošno nižje kot pri motorjih z notranjim zgorevanjem. Za praktično uporabo so paro v veliki meri nadomestili motorji z notranjim zgorevanjem ali elektromotorji. Vendar se večina električne energije proizvaja s parnimi turbinami, tako da je svetovna industrija posredno še vedno odvisna od parnega pogona. Nedavni pomisleki glede virov goriva in onesnaževanja so spodbudili ponovno zanimanje za paro kot sestavni del procesov soproizvodnje in kot glavnega pogona. To postaja znano kot gibanje Advanced Steam.[potreben citat]

column1: Some elements of the Brotherhood, though perhaps against orders, did engage in violence against the government, and its founder Al-Banna was assassinated in 1949 in retaliation for the assassination of Egypt's premier Mahmud Fami Naqrashi three months earlier. The Brotherhood has suffered periodic repression in Egypt and has been banned several times, in 1948 and several years later following confrontations with Egyptian president Gamal Abdul Nasser, who jailed thousands of members for several years.
column2: Nekateri pripadniki bratovščine, čeprav morda proti ukazom, so sodelovali pri nasilju proti vladi, njen ustanovitelj Al-Banna pa je bil leta 1949 umorjen zaradi maščevalnega atentata na egiptovskega premierja Mahmuda Famija Naqrašija tri mesece pred tem. Bratovščina je doživela periodično represijo v Egiptu in je bila večkrat prepovedana, leta 1948 in nekaj let kasneje, po spopadih z egiptovskim predsednikom Gamalom Abdulom Nasserjem, ki je za več let zaprl na tisoče članov.

column1: Kublai Khan promoted commercial, scientific, and cultural growth. He supported the merchants of the Silk Road trade network by protecting the Mongol postal system, constructing infrastructure, providing loans that financed trade caravans, and encouraging the circulation of paper banknotes (鈔, Chao). Pax Mongolica, Mongol peace, enabled the spread of technologies, commodities, and culture between China and the West. Kublai expanded the Grand Canal from southern China to Daidu in the north. Mongol rule was cosmopolitan under Kublai Khan. He welcomed foreign visitors to his court, such as the Venetian merchant Marco Polo, who wrote the most influential European account of Yuan China. Marco Polo's travels would later inspire many others like Christopher Columbus to chart a passage to the Far East in search of its legendary wealth.
column2: Kublajkan je spodbujal gospodarsko, znanstveno in kulturno rast. Trgovce, ki so trgovali na svilni cesti, je podpiral z zaščito mongolskega poštnega sistema, gradnjo infrastrukture, zagotavljanjem posojil, s katerimi so se financirale trgovske prikolice, in spodbujanjem obtoka papirnatih bankovcev (鈔, Chao). Pax Mongolica, mongolski mir, je omogočil širjenje tehnologij, dobrin in kulture med Kitajsko in Zahodom. Kublajkan je razširil Veliki prekop od juga Kitajske do Daiduja na severu. Pod Kubljkanom je bila mongolska vladavina je bila svetovna. Na svojem dvoru je sprejemal tuje obiskovalce, kot je beneški trgovec Marco Polo, ki je napisal najvplivnejšo evropsko kroniko o Kitajski v času dinastije Juan. Potovanja Marca Pola so kasneje navdihnila mnoge druge, kot je Krištof Kolumb, da so se v iskanju legendarnega bogastva odpravili na Daljni vzhod.

column1: Demographically, it was the most diverse city in Poland, with significant numbers of foreign-born inhabitants. In addition to the Polish majority, there was a significant Jewish minority in Warsaw. According to Russian census of 1897, out of the total population of 638,000, Jews constituted 219,000 (around 34% percent). Warsaw's prewar Jewish population of more than 350,000 constituted about 30 percent of the city's total population. In 1933, out of 1,178,914 inhabitants 833,500 were of Polish mother tongue. World War II changed the demographics of the city, and to this day there is much less ethnic diversity than in the previous 300 years of Warsaw's history. Most of the modern day population growth is based on internal migration and urbanisation.
column2: Demografsko je bilo to najbolj raznoliko mesto na Poljskem, z velikim številom prebivalcev, rojenih v tujini. Poleg poljske večine je bila v Varšavi znatna judovska manjšina. Po ruskem popisu prebivalstva iz leta 1897 je bilo od celotnega prebivalstva, ki je štelo 638.000 ljudi, Judov 219.000 (približno 34 %). Predvojna judovska populacija v Varšavi, ki je obsegala več kot 350.000, je predstavljala približno 30 odstotkov celotnega prebivalstva mesta. Leta 1933 je od 1.178.914 prebivalcev poljski jezik za maternega imelo 833.500. Druga svetovna vojna je spremenila demografijo mesta in do danes je etnična raznolikost veliko manjša kot v prejšnjih 300 letih Varšavske zgodovine. Večina rasti prebivalstva v sodobnem času temelji na notranjih migracijah in urbanizaciji.

column1: During this time, the discovery of oil in the North Sea and the following "It's Scotland's oil" campaign of the Scottish National Party (SNP) resulted in rising support for Scottish independence, as well as the SNP. The party argued that the revenues from the oil were not benefitting Scotland as much as they should. The combined effect of these events led to Prime Minister Wilson committing his government to some form of devolved legislature in 1974. However, it was not until 1978 that final legislative proposals for a Scottish Assembly were passed by the United Kingdom Parliament.
column2: V tem času sta odkritje nafte v Severnem morju in kampanja Škotske nacionalne stranke (SNP) s sloganom »Škotska nafta«, ki je sledila, prinesla večjo podporo škotski neodvisnosti in stranki SNP. Ta je trdila, da prihodki od nafte Škotski niso koristili toliko, kot bi morali. Skupni učinek teh dogodkov je privedel do tega, da je predsednik vlade Wilson leta 1974 svojo vlado zavezal neki obliki decentralizirane zakonodaje. Vendar je parlament Združenega kraljestva sprejel končne zakonodajne predloge za škotsko skupščino šele leta 1978.

In the 1970s, the city was the subject of a song, "Walking Into Fresno", written by Hall Of Fame guitarist Bill Aken and recorded by Bob Gallion of the world-famous "WWVA Jamboree" radio and television show in Wheeling, West Virginia. Aken, adopted by Mexican movie actress Lupe Mayorga, grew up in the neighboring town of Madera and his song chronicled the hardships faced by the migrant farm workers he saw as a child. Aken also made his first TV appearance playing guitar on the old country-western show at The Fresno Barn.
column2: V sedemdesetih letih prejšnjega stoletja je bilo mesto predmet pesmi »Walking Into Fresno«, ki jo je napisal kitarist iz dvorane slavnih, Bill Aken, posnel pa jo je Bob Gallion s svetovno znanega radia in televizijske oddaje »WWVA Jamboree« v Wheelingu v Zahodni Virginiji. Aken, ki ga je posvojila mehiška filmska igralka Lupe Mayorga, je odraščal v sosednjem mestu Madera in njegova pesem je opisovala stiske, s katerimi so se soočali migrantski delavci na kmetijah, ki jih je videl kot otrok. Za svoj prvi televizijski nastop  je Aken igral kitaro v stari country vestern oddaji The Fresno Barn.
